SIMPLE: blustering
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blustering
<hw>Blus"ter*ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Exhibiting noisy
violence, as the wind; stormy; tumultuous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A tempest and a <qex>blustering</qex> day.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Uttering noisy threats; noisy and swaggering;
boisterous.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>blustering</xex> fellow.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blusteringly</ent>⟦br⟧
